<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbaad3edc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1397k–3"><num value="1397k–3">§ 1397k–3.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out this subpart—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbaad3edd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1397k–3/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> for fiscal year 2011, $6,500,000; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbaad3ede-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1397k–3/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> for each of fiscal years 2012 through 2014, $7,000,000.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idbaad3edf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531">Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531</ref>, title XX, § 2024, as added <ref href="/us/pl/111/148/tVI/s6703/a/1/C">Pub. L. 111–148, title VI, § 6703(a)(1)(C)</ref>, <date date="2010-03-23">Mar. 23, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/790">124 Stat. 790</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
